<p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/7788702/946679">Psutil suggested by Mark</a>, is really the best solution, its only drawback is the GPL compatible license. If that's a problem, then you can invoke Windows' process info commands: <code>wmic process</code> where WMI is available (XP pro, vista, win7) or <code>tasklist</code>. Here is a description to do it: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/706989/how-to-call-an-external-program-in-python-and-retrieve-the-output-and-return-cod">How to call an external program in python and retrieve the output and return code?</a> (not the only possible way...)</p>
